Introduction

AtHeart is an upcoming girl group under TITAN CONTENT. They are scheduled to make their debut in July 2025.

The groups name 'AtHeart' was formed by combining the words 'Heart' which represents the heart and love, and the word 'At' and the '@' symbol which means connecting to the hearts of fans around the world and the growth, communication into the new world.

On July 16, 2024, TITAN CONTENT announced that they are preparing to debut their first US based girl group with the name AtHeart. In the same article, Billboard revealed that AtHeart will make their debut sometime in the first half of 2025. That same day, the first two members Sorin and Michi were revealed alongside their own individual Instagram accounts in what they called 'NEXT-GENERATION' K-POP STRATEGY.

On November 12, 2024 three members Seohyeon, Katelyn and Aurora were revealed.

On February 19, 2025, Sorin's reveal post and SNS accounts were deleted, indicating her departure from the group. On the same day, the addition of Nahyun, Arin and Bome was announced.

On February 21, 2025 it was reported that AtHeart would be debuting in July 2025 with a seven-member lineup, confirming the departure of Sorin. Their official SNS accounts and debut teaser were revealed on the same day. The group will be releasing a pre-debut single "GoodGirl AtHeart" on March 14.
